product_name: IT CosmeticsBye Bye Dark Spots Concealer + Serum
summary: SummaryIT Cosmetics Bye Bye Dark Spots Concealer + Serum provides instant medium coverage and clinically fades the look of dark spots and other skin concerns over time.
details: DetailsBenefitsAll-in-one dark spots concealer + serum provides buildable, medium coverage with a natural finish to instantly improve the look of dark spots and other skin texture concernsIT Cosmetics partners with plastic surgeons and dermatologists to develop skin-loving solutions and clinically tested formulasFeaturesAFTER 12 WEEKS*:94% say bare skin looks smoother*86% say dark spots look minimized***Based on expert grading after 12 weeks of daily use.Key Ingredients2% Niacinamide: Helps skin look more even-toned; minimizes the look of dark spotsCaffeine: Helps skin look brighterItem 2607707How To UseUsing the doe-foot applicator, tap directly onto the desired areas you want to conceal or brighten.Take the built-in kabuki concealer brush and tap repeatedly (stipple) to blend effortlessly into the skin. For hard-to-reach areas, we also recommend using the IT Brushes for ULTA Airbrush Essential Concealer Brush #144.3.Pair it with CC+ Nude Glow Lightweight Foundation + Glow Serum with SPF 40 for a healthy glow finish. HOW TO CLEAN YOUR MAKEUP BRUSHES: ‚Ä¢ At least once a week, clean the built-in kabuki concealer brush and any other makeup brushes you use with Brush Bath Purifying Makeup Brush Cleaner.IngredientsAqua/Water/Eau Coco-Caprylate/Caprate Hydrogenated Polyisobutene Glycerin, Propanediol, Propylene Glycol, Sorbitan Isostearate, Polyglyceryl-6 Polyricinoleate, Niacinamide, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Hydroxyethylpiperazine Ethane Sulfonic Acid, Phenoxyethanol, Magnesium Sulfate, Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate, Paraffin, Hydroxyacetophenone, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Cera Microcristallina/Microcrystalline Wax/Cire Microcristalline, Caprylyl Glycol Silica Silylate Silica, Synthetic Wax, Caffeine, Centella Asiatica Extract, Trisodium Ethylenediamine Disuccinate, Aluminum Hydroxide, Tocopherol, Adenosine, Sodium Hyaluronate, Hydrated Silica, Helianthus Annuus Seed Oil/Sunflower Seed Oil, Methicone.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Using the doe-foot applicator, tap directly onto the desired areas you want to conceal or brighten.Take the built-in kabuki concealer brush and tap repeatedly (stipple) to blend effortlessly into the skin. For hard-to-reach areas, we also recommend using the IT Brushes for ULTA Airbrush Essential Concealer Brush #144.3.Pair it with CC+ Nude Glow Lightweight Foundation + Glow Serum with SPF 40 for a healthy glow finish. HOW TO CLEAN YOUR MAKEUP BRUSHES: ‚Ä¢ At least once a week, clean the built-in kabuki concealer brush and any other makeup brushes you use with Brush Bath Purifying Makeup Brush Cleaner.

reviews.headline: Best concealer I've used
reviews.comments: The color blends perfectly with my skin. And I can see some of my dark spots starting to fade. I don't even use the foundation anymore. Just the concealer. It apply smoothly and blends well.

reviews.headline: Poor design of tube
reviews.comments: Product seems ok but I cannot tolerate a leaking product. Other brands have a magnetic click in to prevent leaking. Also having a brush built into the tube may seem handy but makes it more difficult to properly clean the brush to prevent bacteria buildup and contamination and skin or eye breakouts. IT should rework this design.

reviews.headline: This was awful; the worst I've ever used.
reviews.comments: This was awful; the worst I've ever used.  The coverage was meh. The content went all over the outside of the container every time I used it. I'd wash it off and the same thing happened the next time. I threw it away. The best part about it was the brush which deserves the "one star".

reviews.headline: I would buy this again and I have!
reviews.comments: It does a great job of covering dark spots

reviews.headline: Purchased again
reviews.comments: I really like the blending brush on this product.  Apparently, IT is introducing a new blending brush on the new one, as this one is phased out..  Although i didn't really need this right now, I wanted to be able to have a new one with the blending brush I like.

reviews.headline: The best concealer I've ever tried!
reviews.comments: I really love this concealer for under eyes. It is light and does not cake or crease on me & I am 52.  I pat it in and it just sets perfectly.  Truly love this.  I'm using the light neutral and it is the best shade for light/semi medium skin with pink & neutral undertones.  Summer time I could probably go one step up.

reviews.headline: Not for me
reviews.comments: I'm a full coverage girlie and this concealer is just not there. The smell was really weird too. Like not musty but dusty as if you found an old book or something. Not sure if that was just mine or if that's how they all smell. Great skincare benefits though!

reviews.headline: it works!
reviews.comments:
I wasn't too optimistic about this product and figured what's one more concealer to try and add to the collection.
The few times I've worn this, it did not settle in the lines or fade.
I was pleasantly surprised.

reviews.headline: Bad coverage
reviews.comments: For me it covered my spots for about an hour with and without primer.  Also tried 2 different kinds of foundation and setting spray.This product does not work well for me.

reviews.headline: Good eye coverage
reviews.comments: I use this under my eyes; I don't have dark eyes bags but dark enough for me to notice.  This is a light coverage for me to even my skin tone.

reviews.headline: Shade range is not good
reviews.comments: I have fair and cool toned skin. The lightest shade Ulta offers is far too orange and dark. If im spending this much on a concealer i shouldnt have to "make it work" for me! Formula is not bad though, but for a high end brand the shades should be better.

reviews.headline: Love it
reviews.comments: Coverage is great, not heavy or thick. Easy to blend.

reviews.headline: Not for textured skin!!!
reviews.comments: I have try this concealer with a lot of different formulas just to give it a chance because i think is a good product BUT unfortunately (and not surprisingly) it does not work if you have textured skin. I think this would work great for dry, mature, maybe even for normal skin, but if you have oily, combination and specially textured skin this is not for you!!! Also, because of all the hydrating ingredients it has, you have to think twice which primer and foundation use it with because if not, it will separate.

reviews.headline: Best concealer so far!
reviews.comments: I'm always searching for the holy grail of concealers, so far this is my first choice. Not only did it offer great coverage, it did not look dry on my skin. The coverage lasted most of the day without soaking into my skin. I really like the brush applicator on the tube, no need to use an additional brush or sponge. I can keep it in my purse and refresh as needed.

reviews.headline: Best Concealer Ever!!
reviews.comments: I have tried so many concealers‚Ä¶from Natasha Denona to Haus Labs‚Ä¶.this beats them all! Color and match is perfection and thr coverage is lovely!!!

reviews.headline: It does cover the dark spots
reviews.comments: IT products are great, but this is one of their best in the line.  I would buy it again.

reviews.headline: Great coverage but not for my skin
reviews.comments: Concealer has effective coverage and good texture. Unfortunately, it has caused significant cystic breakouts in the areas i used it (around nostrils, chin and between brows. Cannot recommend because of this.

reviews.headline: Glides nicely but not enough coverage
reviews.comments: I wish it was more effective, i found myself adding more and more to cover dark circles but it's not as builable. Nice feel on the skin and can work if you need less coverage.

reviews.headline: Coverage only OK
reviews.comments: This does not cover well and the more important thing is that it comes off easily.  It does not last through the day. I would not recommend it.

reviews.headline: I AM BUYING ANOTHER AS BACK UP!  I DON'T WANT TO RUN OUT!
reviews.comments: I LOVE THIS!!! I do not ever want to be without it!  I use it for a couple dark spots on my cheek and as a concealer under my eyes. It really works well and you can't tell I have anything on. I like to use Bare Minerals powder foundation most every day & the two work really well together

media.headline: Replaced my Old Concealer
media.caption:
Thank you BzzAgent and IT Cosmetics for #gifting me this IT BYE BYE DARK SPOTS CONCEALER AND SERUM in medium warm 32. 

üí• Instant Medium Coverage 
üí• 24 hours of hydration
üí• Developed with dermatologists and plastic surgeons, safe for sensitive skin
üí•Vegan 
üí• Fades dark spots, fine lines, dark circles under eyes and uneven skin texture
üí• Contains 2% niacinamide, hyaluronic acid and caffeine

This went on smooth with the doe foot applicator, and blended so easily with the attached Kabuki brush. The Kabuki brush was an extremely high quality. It may be one of the best brushes I have ever used. The product concealed well and left the areas, that I used it in, hydrated and smoothed. It did not crease or transfer color. It stayed from morning on into the night without fading or flaking. I think the serum in it plays an active role in keeping it crease proof. Overall, it's a great product and I will repurchase again. I am actually going to replace my previous concealer brand that I have used for years with this one.  #bzzagentcampaign #itcosmetics #bzzagents #makeup #concealer #serum #skincare #influencer #reviewer #producttester #skincareroutine

faceoff_positive.comments: I just purchased my 2 bottle of this concealer for the dreaded under eye dark circles. I have tried many concealers as we all have I'm sure and this was the one that worked best for me. I'm 49, VERY fair, neutral skin tone and I wear shade fair neutral 11. (IT Cosmetics shade matched me and nailed it, (I wear a little Halo Glow skin tint but I do not wear foundation) normal skin tone, blue eyes, dark brown hair. Can't imagine how perfect this would look if I did wear foundation but it just doesn't look good on my mature skin. This concealer does give that serum feel but is still pretty thick, perfect consistency for me. Also, I've tried every method for applying and the built in brush does work best but Pat, Pat, Pat, don't swipe. It also helps with sun spots or any thing that you're trying to conceal. I lucked out and got it 50% off this time but would pay full price. The 1 thing I find odd is the packaging since it has a rounded bottom so you can stand it up. No biggie but strange nevertheless. This is the first time I have EVER added pics to a review or anything bc I hate my pic taken. Hope it helps someone.  I was not incentivized to write this review but I wish I was üòÖ! I Love IT's concealer, superhero mascara is another must have for me.
faceoff_positive.headline: Great for mature under eyes‚Ä¶

faceoff_negative.comments: I wanted to love this because it is such a pretty coverage but it ends up drying out after wearing for a short while and then you can see it breaking up on the skin and it's very noticeable. Makes me sad because I love it otherwise!
faceoff_negative.headline: I give it a 6/10
